casebody.data:
Eudolph SCHULENBERG, Appellant, v. UNITED STATES of America, Appellee. Circuit Court of Appeals, Ninth Circuit. March 19, 1934. Anthony Savage, U. S. Atty., and De Witt C. Rowland, Asst. U. S. Atty., both of Seattle, Wash.

Before WILBUE and SAWTELLE, Circuit Judges, and NOECROSS, District Judge.

PEE CURIAM.

Upon motion of counsel for appellee, ordered appeal dismissed for failure of appellant to file record and docket cause; mandate forthwith.
